The units are used to help manage field (operational) activities and are used to summarise environmental attributes of the overall Water Supply Area.

idCitation.resTitle: Greater Victoria Water Supply Area Vegetation Resource Inventory

dataIdInfo.idAbs:
In 2011-2012, the CRD contracted Forest Dimensions Inc (FDI) to conduct Phase 1 vegetation resource inventory for the Greater Victoria Water Supply Area. Data was collected following Phase 1 data collection standards. This data was submitted to the provincial government for inclusion in their province-wide VRI dataset. The province then added some derived attributes including label fields, aging and growing the forest. Phase 2 was not completed.

This provincial data was extracted back to the CRD for further modifications by re-populating the original unique ID supplied by FDI, other CRD specific attributes and to add in some missing polygons. For the missing polygons, best efforts were made to fill in the provincially derived fields that were relevant to the CRD such as labeling and projected age and height. It is hoped these polygons will be formally included in the provincial data in January 2017.

Data is divided into 2 feature classes - WSAVRITreeLYR1 and TreeLYR2, representing the various tree layers existing in the forest stand.
